description: Go to New Relic to sign up and get your license key at http://newrelic.com or you can get a license key through the Windows Azure management portal via Add-On store.
releaseNotes:
New Features

* Removes prompting for the license key from the install process.  In a recent release of the Microsoft Azure Portal an update has been made so that users can go to the WebSite Project in the portal > Configuration > Developer Analytics and either choose the New Relic add on there or simply add a license key.  All previous methods of using the license key still work but this feature allows a "no touch" package-install for Azure Web Sites
summary: This package will add all of the resources needed to profile your Windows Azure Web Site running as a reserved 64-bit instance. For more information on this package visit: https://newrelic.com/docs/dotnet/azure-web-sites
title: New Relic for Windows Azure Web Sites (x64)
